<h1>Special Functions</h1>
<p>
  Most places that talk about special functions usually consider functions like: Airy, Bessel, Chebyshev, and Lagendre, 
  but here we will consider a different class
  of special funcitons. Instead of considering special functions that
  are the solutions of differential equations, as most of those just
  mentioned are, we will be considering functions such as ppV(x)ppSupV(x)
  or the iteration of such functions. The function ppV(x)ppSupV(x) is
  notoriously difficult to iterate, expecially in a smooth manner.
  For more information about continuous iteration, 
  click on the iteration tab above.
</p>
